amend /əˈmɛnd/

(amending,amended,amends) 

1. V-T If you amend something that has been written such as a law, or something that is said, you change it in order to improve it or make it more accurate. 修正 

例： The president agreed to amend the constitution and allow multi-party elections. 总统同意了修正宪法并且允许多党选举。 

2. PHRASE If you make amends when you have harmed someone, you show that you are sorry by doing something to please them. 做补偿 

例： He wanted to make amends for causing their marriage to fail. 他想为一手造成他们婚姻的破裂做出补偿。

